<br>
How is that type of relationship healthy? I know you are going on the bible and doing what it says....but that isn't an answer. How is it healthy? <br>
<br>
I would get ticked off living like that. I am an equal in this marriage even if I do fullfill the traditional wife role. But I have equal say in all matters. We couldn't respect each other any other way. We can respect our children, its our job to raise them and part of raising them is making their choices for them. But I couldn't respect my husband if I knew he would accept my final say in all matters. And he wouldn't respect me for the same thing.  It wouldn't matter if he usually LET me have my way or if he treated me like a queen. Just knowing that I would always back down if he instisted (and viceversa) would kill our mutual respect. <br>
<br>
But then I look long and hard for a man who could stand up to me. I've a very forceful personality. And its nice to buttheads. It makes us both stronger.<br>
